text: We're searchin' for a beast of yore with a long neck and a tail
Everywhere we look we lose on this long and dusty trail...
We're westward ho 'cause the ranchers know somethin' isn't right
Their goats are being snatched away in the darkness of the night... (Chupacabra ho...)
I'm not usually a crier, But isn't that-
Posses and gangs have tried to hunt and flush it from its lair, But not 'til now have a gang of kids pursued it from the air...
Cowboys tried to trap and trick it with just about everything, But no one's ever tried to lure it with a bully on a string.
